author: Jen 🌹
text:
You killed 3 characters with one stone and it's something unforgivable. 
How do you feel about sounding like an absolute madwoman and wreck the whoe meaning of the show in the final 4 minutes?

author: Jen 🌹
text: Because if you did, you wouldn't be so proud about the destruction you just caused using the same old tropes which in this case didn't even mean anything. Kudos to you Laura Neal for delivering the most meaningless and cruel death to not only V but also Eve and Carolyn.

author: Jen 🌹
text: Reading those interviews makes my blood boil, like how one person can be soooo clueless to the core story of the show when they claimed they were a  fan of it since the beginning.

author: Jen 🌹
text:
I'm literally disgusted about myself being once a firmly believer that Laura Neal would make everything right when it comes to the characters and us as viewers based on the work she did on s3. 
Because that was the most utter betrayal anyone could ever have.
Cruelty all around.
